  Locus:
    Page: 402
    Verse: 15
Tags:
  - Saints
---
Saints have a habit of saying that they feel themselves to be no
better than the vilest sinners, and they are right. Scoundrels and saints
stand equal in the opposite pans of one and the same balance.
